@node "requerimentos" "Requirements..."

 @{b}For running Zelador you'll need:@{ub}


 - any Amiga chipset, 68000 minimum, few KBs of memory (+ mem spent by MUI)

 - Amiga OS 2.1 (3.0 or higher recommended)

 - MUI 3.3 (or better) - available in Aminet.

 - Miami 1.0 (or better) running at time
   * Zelador, perhaps, may support other TCP stacks in future

 - YAM 1.3 (or better) running at time or
   YAM 2.0 @{b}preview 7 of better@{ub}
   * Zelador, perhaps, may support other mailers in future
@endnode

@node "Registrando" "Freeware"



 ZELADOR IS FREEWARE NOW
 -----------------------

   Why am i releasing Zelador for free now?

   That's because no-one cares about it, even Zelador being a 5-dollars'
shareware software.

   The fact is that I CAN'T COMPETE with a guy from a rich country like
France or Germany who receives money FOR studying in university with free
time for releasing good free software just for fun!

   Amiga is full of software designed by such type of people!


   Sorry pal, but i live in a country which, WITH LUCK, you can get a job so
you're able to sustain yourself and buy food. Here a computer is 10 times
harder for buying than for a west-european Richie-Rich.
   Being a programmer is not a cheap thing, you need to invest money for
books/etc and lots, lots of time.. and, believe me, time IS money. (in case
of Amiga, lost money)

   Well.. just ONE user registered Zelador, can you believe it? Only ~5
people requested register information.. and absolutely no
congrats/bug-report/whatever messages.. i'm being treated by Amiga users
JUST LIKE Windoze users but with a difference: i'm not receiving a single
cent of dollar.


   Looking behind i see where Windoze is and where could i be as a
programmer if i decided for a PC in 1990 instead, in that moment, that great
A500.
   Now i'm a looser just because i'm a good programer but for the wrong OS,
while there's a Visual Crap Basic stupid brainless unexperienced kid is
receiving good money and fame for his crap softwares.
   I'm not receiving money and i have absolutely zero moral rewards from
Amiga community (as if i were the only shareware programmer with this
problem) so what's the point developing for Amiga? No one cares.

   I'm no longer developing a single line of code for Amiga OS (or that
pseudo-Amiga that MooMoo's Amiga NG).


   After C= failure, Escom failure and MooMoo's 2-years-long talking about
NG and kicking original Amiga technology i finally gave up.

   And about these brazilian Amiga users (and brazilians in general).. what
could i say about them, not using a single bad word?


   There's a limit even for the most optimistic and determined man in Earth.
Mine's reached.

.
@endnode

