@node "Futuro" "Future..."

 @{b}Ideas for future development of Zelador:@{ub}



 This is the last version of Zelador.



 Here goes the things i thought adding but are not going to see the light.

 The simple ones:

 - Add locale support.
 - Support other TCP stacks than Miami.
 - Support other mailers than YAM.

 The complex ones:

 - FTP Robot. It gets ftp directory so, with its GUI, you can select all
   what you want to download.
 - HTTP Robot. Given http paths is recover the pages automatically and, if
   defined, it seek for the linked pages too (1, 2, 3.. levels down.
   configurable). Yes/No to GIF/JPG/LHA/ZIP/etc.
   With this the user could browse the desired pages cached in HD.

 .
@endnode

@node "Historia" "Program History"

 @{b}Development History:@{ub}



 @{b}0.8▀@{ub}  - First public release.

 @{b}0.85▀@{ub} - Inter-application communication system was totally rewritten;
         now Zelador will not lock if Miami or YAM locks up.

       - Fixed a bug which permitted Zelador being closed while
         event running.

       - Fixed the bug of 'Force Event' which made it work only
         few times; now it works always.

       - Fixed a bug which caused Zelador to think that Miami
         connection was stablished even when it wasn't.
         (now it redials normally when busy, no dialtone, etc)

       - Added detection if Miami/YAM is active in memory;
         it pops a promting window if not.

 @{b}0.86▀@{ub} - If YAM returned error Zelador stays connected until
         time limit expires. (New bug from 0.85▀) Fixed.
         Not released for public (1 bug fixed, 10 added.. how i'm lazy.)

 @{b}1.0@{ub}   - First non-beta release.

       - Added the Email File Request feature.

       - Added the Robot Reply feature.

       - Added logging (three separated files)

       - Setup window was completely revised.

       - Fixed the bug in the time management: if the event was defined
         such way it could cross the midnight connected (ex.: 2300 to 0400)
         Zelador would incorrectly abort it just after the TCP connection
         is stablished. (i typed the name of the wrong variable.. sh..)

       - All known bugs from 0.85▀ and 0.86▀ fixed.

       - Shareware limitation changed: saving setup is allowed now, but
         both Email File Request and Robot Reply are limited to 1 file
         each.
         Registered users can use all the file slots of both.

 @{b}1.1@{ub}   - Fixed the bug which caused Zelador thinking that YAM (2.x) wasn't
         active even if it was in memory running.

       - Fixed minor bugs of Setup GUI which permmited the user to enter
         invalid characters in certain fields.

       - Minor enhancements in Setup GUI.

       - Fixed the bug which made Zelador to crash in some situations:
         stack underdimensioned. (why are the worst-to-track bugs the
         stupidest ones?)

       - NOW Zelador is truly 68000 compatible: i was compiling it for 000
         but using 020-compiled link includes. I think that Zelador will
         not guru when starting on 68000 (i couldn't really test.. i lost
         contact with the only 000 Zelador user i knew, who reported this
         problem).

 @{b}1.2@{ub}   - Retaken development of Zelador after 10 months.

       - First Aminet release.

       - Now YAM 2.x is truly supported (Zelador is still compatible with
         Yam 1.x anyway). Some changes in code were necessary.

       - A minor bug in GUI management corrected.

 @{b}1.21@{ub}  - Incredible silly bug fixed.
         When forcing 'RobotReply' processing (by menu activation) was the
         'EmailFileRequest' which was activated. -- I wrote the name of
         wrong procedure.

 @{b}1.22@{ub}  - Free release of Zelador.
         There are no code differences between 1.21 and 1.22 except for the
         key checker code, which was completely removed.
         Full source code included.

.
@endnode

@node "ConfEvents" "Events"

 @{b}@{fg shine}Events@{ub}@{fg text}
 things what you want and don't want Zelador doing



   - @{b}Auto Miami@{ub}        : normally checked, if not Zelador will not try
                         to connect/disconnect automatically with Miami.
                         @{i}Disable this if you have a 24h dedicated internet
                         connection (so it's not necessary to dial)@{ui}

   - @{b}Receive YAM mails@{ub} : normally checked, if not Zelador will not get
                         YAM mails.
                         @{i}Usually you will want it enabled.@{ui}

   - @{b}Send YAM mails@{ub}    : normally checked, if not Zelador will not send
                         YAM mails.
                         @{i}Usually you will want it enabled.@{ui}

   - @{b}Auto Process Email File Request@{ub} : check it if you want to process the
     |                   email file requests automatically.
     |
     `- @{b}Run it while connected@{ub} : if checked, process requests and send them
                         while connected; if not, process after Miami
                         disconnection.
                         @{i}Your decision: immediate reply for new messages at
                         cost of being connected while processing or
                         short-as-possible phone calls and reply delayed to
                         next event.@{ui}

   - @{b}Auto Process Robot Reply@{ub}  : check it if you want to process the robot
     |                    reply requests automatically.
     |
     `- @{b}Run it while connected@{ub} : if checked, process requests and send them
                         while connected; if not, process after Miami
                         disconnection.
                         @{i}Your decision: immediate reply for new messages at
                         cost of being connected while processing or
                         short-as-possible phone calls and reply delayed to
                         next event.@{ui}


   - @{b}Programmable events@{ub}: CLI commands/programs you want to be executed
                          automatically by Zelador.

     Active     - command will be executed or not.

     Text field - command line (as if you were typing in CLI)

     Wait       - if checked, wait until command returns.
                  WARNING: if enabled and command never returns
                  Zelador will never returns too!


 .
@endnode

@node "ConfTimes" "Times"

 @{b}@{fg shine}Times@{ub}@{fg text}
 determines when and how long Zelador will do things



   (24h format used here)

   - @{b}Limit connection by@{ub} .... : limits the maximum connection, Zelador will
                                force disconnection if transfers aren't
                                complete when the limit is reached.

     maximum length - limit connection to HHMM minutes of length.
                      ex.: 0130 (will be '1:30h long')

     maximum time   - force disconnection after this HHMM time.
                      ex.: 2140 (will be 'until 9:40 PM')

   - @{b}Event begins at@{ub}: when (HHMM) Zelador will start to try to connect.
                      ex.: 0100 (starts at 1:00 AM)

   - @{b}Try until@{ub}: try to connect up to HHMM, after this Zelador gives up.
                      ex.: 0115 (if not connected until 1:15 AM, gives up)

 .
@endnode

@node "ConfEFR" "Email File Request"

 @{b}@{fg shine}Email File Request@{ub}@{fg text}
 file server by email: people can get files you offer

  @{b}Note:@{ub} When Email File Request starts processing your mails YAM will be
automatically iconified for minimizing the processing time. (otherwise it
would be bloodly slow.. :-/)

  @{b}Note (2):@{ub} Email File Request will @{b}NOT@{ub} process e-mails with 'R' (reply)
status, but it'll delete them aswell.

   - @{b}Subject text to intercept@{ub} : string you want to be reserved and
         intercepted 'subject' field of message.
         You probably may want to use something like:
         "FILE REQUEST" or "FILES OF DAN".
         NOT case sensitive.

   - @{b}Presentation text@{ub}         : filename of text you want to be
         sent when user makes the request.
         Here you inform user how to request the files; just below
         this text appears the file list.

   - @{b}Sending file text@{ub}         : filename of text you want to be
         sent with the attached files the user requested.

   - @{b}Max Request Kb per Event@{ub}  : limits to XXX Kb of requested
         files per processing. Other requests will remain untouched
         until next processing.
         * Note that if you process twice (as example) with limit
           defined to 6000 (6 Mb) you may have up to 12Mb of
           messages to send at once. Define it according your
           dialy message Kb sending capacity.

   - @{b}Start to refuse at Kb@{ub}     : if file requests exceedes this
         limit Zelador will start to simply delete the following
         'file request' messages. This is the extreme protection
         against flooding.
            You may want to leave it as big as possible.

   - @{b}Max ID age to accept@{ub}      : each file request, when user
         receives the file listing, there's an ID coming together
         with the subject of message; this is the protection
         against people who tries to make file requests
         with fake email address.
            Here you define how long (days) the given ID will
         remain valid for requesting files with that.
         Five days seems a good lifetime, but you can change
         according your needs.



 (table)

   - @{b}Available@{ub}                 : Activated if file is available.

   - @{b}File Description@{ub}          : String describing the file.
         This appears in the file listing and when the file is
         being sent.
         ex.: The 1st place in music contest at Ugabuga Party 1998!

   - @{b}File (full path required)@{ub} : The file itself.
         ex.: dh1:archives/music/MVP.mod

 .
@endnode

@node "ConfRR" "Robot Reply"

 @{b}@{fg shine}Robot Reply@{ub}@{fg text}
 reply automatically messages containing specified subject


  @{b}Note:@{ub} When Robot Reply starts processing your mails YAM will be
automatically iconified for minimizing the processing time. (otherwise it
would be bloodly slow.. :-/)

  @{b}Note (2):@{ub} Robot Reply will @{b}NOT@{ub} process e-mails with 'R' (reply) status,
but it'll delete them aswell.


 no secret here.. it's just a table!

    - @{b}Enabled@{ub}            : Checked if you want to intercept the topic and
                           send the message, unchecked if not.

    - @{b}Topic to Intercept@{ub} : Messages containing this string subject will
                           be automatically replied.
                           NOT case sensitive.
                           ex.: COMPUTER PRICE LIST REQUEST

    - @{b}Text File@{ub}          : The textfile to send to user.
                           ex.: dh1:documents/biz/PriceList-Updated.txt


 .
@endnode

